"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_36" = "What will you gain by staying up?";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_37" = "Rest is not laziness. It's recovery.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_38" = "Close the app. Open your dreams.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_39" = "Your body keeps score. It's counting right now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_40" = "You already know you should sleep.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_41" = "Every great day starts the night before.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_42" = "Your phone doesn't care about you. Your bed does.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_43" = "Three deep breaths. Then lights out.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_44" = "Nothing good happens after midnight on a phone.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_45" = "Screen time is stealing your life time.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_46" = "Discipline is choosing sleep over scrolling.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_47" = "You deserve a good night's sleep.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_48" = "The world will still be there tomorrow.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_49" = "Sleep is when your brain sorts everything out.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_50" = "Put it down. You won't miss anything.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_51" = "This moment decides tomorrow's mood.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_52" = "Your willpower is at zero. Just stop.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_53" = "Charge your phone. Charge yourself.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_54" = "Sleep deprivation ages you faster.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_55" = "Be kind to future you. Sleep now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_56" = "Scrolling won't solve tomorrow's problems.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_57" = "Your immune system works while you sleep.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_58" = "Phone in another room. Head on pillow.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_59" = "Winners sleep. Losers scroll.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_notification_60" = "Last chance. Put it down.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_22" = "Nothing you're reading or watching right now will matter tomorrow. But the sleep you skip will affect your focus, mood, and health. Put the phone away.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_23" = "Your pillow doesn't judge. Your pillow doesn't need Wi-Fi. Walk to your bed, lie down, and let go. Tomorrow starts when you close your eyes tonight.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_24" = "Future you is watching this moment. They're either grateful you slept or angry you didn't. Make them proud. Screen off, eyes closed, done.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_25" = "Stop reading. Put your phone face down. Take three slow breaths through your nose. Feel the tension leave. That's your body saying thank you.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_26" = "Your brain consolidates memories, repairs neurons, and flushes toxins during sleep. Scrolling blocks all of that. Give your brain what it needs.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_27" = "The dopamine from that next video lasts 3 seconds. A good night's sleep powers 16 hours. The math is obvious. Choose wisely.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_28" = "Sleep-deprived people eat 300 more calories, have 40% less emotional control, and make 20% worse decisions. Is that who you want to be tomorrow?";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_29" = "Nighttime regret compounds. Each lost hour tonight creates a chain of bad choices tomorrow. Break the cycle by putting your phone on the charger now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_30" = "Your alarm doesn't care how late you stayed up. 6 AM comes regardless. The only variable is how you feel when it rings. Choose well.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_31" = "8 hours of sleep returns 16 hours of peak performance. No supplement, app, or hack comes close. Invest in yourself. Go to bed.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_32" = "Whatever happened today is done. Reviewing it won't change it. But sleeping on it literally helps your brain process and file it away. Let it go.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_33" = "Sleep debt is real. You're writing checks your body can't cash. Every minute awake past your bedtime costs double tomorrow. Stop the bleeding.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_34" = "Social media is engineered to keep you scrolling. The algorithm wins when you lose sleep. Take back control. Close the app and close your eyes.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_35" = "Your eyes are dry, heavy, and strained. That's not tiredness—it's damage accumulating. Give them 8 hours of recovery. Screen off now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_36" = "Ask yourself: What will I gain by staying up 30 more minutes? Now ask: What will I lose? The answer is always the same. Sleep wins.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_37" = "Rest is not wasted time. Your muscles rebuild, your immune system strengthens, and your creativity recharges. Sleep is doing something. Go do it.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_38" = "Close every app. Set your alarm. Place your phone across the room. Get under the covers. Breathe deeply three times. You're free.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_39" = "Cortisol rises with every late night. Your body is keeping score—higher stress, weaker immunity, faster aging. Stop paying the toll. Sleep now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_40" = "You didn't need this notification to know you should sleep. You already knew. The hard part is acting on what you know. Act now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_41" = "Peak performers protect their sleep. Athletes, CEOs, surgeons—they all know sleep is the foundation. Build your tomorrow on solid ground.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_42" = "Your phone is designed to extract attention. Your bed is designed to restore you. Choose the thing that actually cares about your wellbeing.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_43" = "Three deep breaths through your nose, six seconds each. Feel your heart rate drop. That's your parasympathetic system saying it's safe to sleep.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_44" = "Late-night decisions are unreliable. Late-night snacks are regrettable. Late-night scrolling is pointless. Everything after midnight on a phone is a loss.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_45" = "Every minute on your phone after bedtime is a minute stolen from your life. Not figuratively—literally. Screen time replaces irreplaceable rest time.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_46" = "Discipline isn't about forcing yourself to wake up early. It's about choosing to sleep when your phone says stay. Choose discipline right now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_47" = "You work hard. You push through tough days. You deserve the recovery that only sleep provides. Don't deny yourself what you've earned.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_48" = "The news, the posts, the messages—they'll all be there at 7 AM. The only thing that won't be there if you stay up is your energy.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_49" = "During deep sleep, your brain replays the day's events and strengthens useful connections. Skip sleep, skip learning. Your brain needs this.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_50" = "FOMO is fake. You're not missing anything. The only real thing you're missing right now is the sleep your body is desperately asking for.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_51" = "Your mood tomorrow is decided right now. Sleep = calm, focused, resilient. No sleep = irritable, foggy, reactive. Pick your tomorrow.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_52" = "Willpower depletes throughout the day. Right now yours is empty. Don't rely on willpower—rely on routine. Put the phone down automatically.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_53" = "Plug in your phone across the room. It charges while you charge. You both wake up at 100%. Simple, effective, done.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_54" = "Chronic sleep loss accelerates skin aging, cognitive decline, and weight gain. Every late night adds up. Stop the compounding damage tonight.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_55" = "Future you needs your help right now. They need energy, clarity, and patience. The only way to give them that is to sleep. Be kind. Go.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_56" = "You're looking at your phone hoping it'll fix something. It won't. Sleep actually fixes things—mood, memory, and perspective. Try the real fix.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_57" = "While you sleep, your immune system produces cytokines that fight infection and inflammation. Skip sleep, skip your body's best defense.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_58" = "Phone goes to the charger in another room. You go to bed. No bargaining, no exceptions. This is the move. Make it now.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_59" = "The people you admire most sleep well. They protect their rest fiercely. The people who scroll until 2 AM? They struggle. Choose your team.";
"nudge_staying_up_late_detail_60" = "This is the last thing you'll read tonight. Not because you have to stop, but because you're choosing to. Screen off. Goodnight.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — cant_wake_up (15-60)
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_15" = "The snooze button is a trap.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_16" = "Your dreams can wait. Your life can't.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_17" = "Cold water. Face. Now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_18" = "10 seconds of discomfort beats 10 hours of regret.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_19" = "The bed is lying to you. Get up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_20" = "Champions wake up when it's hard.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_21" = "Your body is ready. Your mind is stalling.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_22" = "Vertical wins. Get upright.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_23" = "Count backwards: 5, 4, 3, 2, 1. Move.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_24" = "The hardest part is the first 60 seconds.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_25" = "Snooze = lose. Get up and win.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_26" = "Your morning routine is waiting for you.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_27" = "One foot on the floor. That's all it takes.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_28" = "The warm bed is a cage. Break free.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_29" = "Every extra minute in bed steals from your day.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_30" = "You'll feel amazing in 10 minutes. Trust the process.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_31" = "Morning light resets your brain. Go get it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_32" = "Your alarm went off for a reason.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_33" = "Sleeping in won't make you less tired.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_34" = "Gravity is your friend. Let your legs hang off the bed.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_35" = "The world needs you awake today.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_36" = "You set this alarm. Trust past you.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_37" = "Every great morning starts with getting up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_38" = "Comfort zone or growth? Choose now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_39" = "Your body adapts. Make mornings a habit.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_40" = "Stretch your arms overhead. Feel alive.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_41" = "The earlier you rise, the more you own your day.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_42" = "Snoozing fragments sleep. It makes you MORE tired.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_43" = "Think about one thing you're excited to do today.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_44" = "Your future self set this alarm. Don't betray them.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_45" = "Wake up or waste up. Your call.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_46" = "Drink water. Your brain is dehydrated.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_47" = "Three stretches. That's your only job right now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_48" = "The morning belongs to the brave.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_49" = "Sitting up is half the battle. Do it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_50" = "Every second in bed past your alarm is a choice.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_51" = "Rise before the excuses do.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_52" = "Your goals don't have a snooze button.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_53" = "Fresh air is one window away.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_54" = "You chose this wake-up time for a reason.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_55" = "Movement creates energy. Start moving.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_56" = "Today has gifts for you. Go find them.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_57" = "Splash cold water. Instant clarity.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_58" = "The pillow is a liar. It says 5 more minutes but means 50.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_59" = "Stand up. The rest is easy.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_notification_60" = "This is your life. Wake up to it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_15" = "Every snooze cycle puts you in lighter sleep, making you groggier. You actually feel worse after snoozing. Get up now and you'll feel better in 5 minutes.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_16" = "While you sleep in, the day starts without you. Opportunities, energy, sunlight—all slipping away. Swing your legs over the edge and stand up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_17" = "Walk to the bathroom. Splash cold water on your face. The cold triggers your sympathetic nervous system. You'll be alert in 30 seconds. Go.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_18" = "The discomfort of getting up lasts less than a minute. The regret of a wasted morning lasts all day. Choose the shorter pain.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_19" = "Your bed feels warm and safe, but it's holding you back. Everything good today happens outside those sheets. Push the covers off. Stand up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_20" = "The people who achieve their goals don't feel like getting up either. They just do it. Feeling follows action. Get up first, feel good second.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_21" = "Your circadian rhythm is ready. Cortisol has peaked. Your body has done its part. Now it's your turn. Sit up and put your feet on the floor.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_22" = "Stand up straight. Raise your arms overhead. Take one deep breath. That's it—you're awake. The hardest part is already done.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_23" = "The 5-4-3-2-1 method works because it bypasses your prefrontal cortex. Don't think about getting up. Just count and move. Go now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_24" = "After 60 seconds of being upright, your brain releases enough cortisol to feel alert. You just need to survive one minute. Start the countdown.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_25" = "Snoozing 3 times means you've chosen to start your day in failure mode. Zero snoozes means you've already won your first battle. Choose victory.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_26" = "Your morning routine is the foundation of your day. Every minute you delay pushes everything else back. Start the dominoes. Get up now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_27" = "Just one foot on the cold floor. That sensation will jolt you awake. Don't think, just drop one foot off the bed. The rest follows naturally.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_28" = "The bed feels warm because your body has heated it all night. That warmth is a trap—it signals sleep, not wakefulness. Escape the warmth.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_29" = "Calculate: 10 extra minutes × 365 days = 60+ hours per year spent snoozing. That's 2.5 full days. What could you do with 2.5 extra days?";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_30" = "In 10 minutes, your adenosine levels will drop and you'll feel genuinely awake. But only if you get up now. Stay in bed and the grogginess persists.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_31" = "Walk to the nearest window. Pull back the curtain. Morning light hitting your retinas suppresses melatonin instantly. Use nature's alarm.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_32" = "You set that alarm with a clear mind and a goal in sight. The groggy version of you doesn't get to override the motivated version. Honor your plan.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_33" = "Extra sleep after your alarm is fragmented and low-quality. It doesn't refresh you—it confuses your body. You're not gaining rest, you're losing time.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_34" = "Let gravity help. Slide your legs to the edge. Let them hang off. Feel the weight pulling you upright. Don't fight physics—use it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_35" = "Someone out there needs your energy today. A friend, a colleague, a family member. They're counting on the awake, present version of you. Show up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_36" = "Last night, you made a promise to yourself by setting this alarm. Breaking promises to yourself erodes self-trust. Keep this one. Get up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_37" = "No great morning ever started with 'I'll get up in 5 more minutes.' Every great morning started with someone deciding to move. Be that person now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_38" = "Comfort zones don't produce growth. The discomfort of the cold floor under your feet is the price of becoming stronger. Pay it gladly.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_39" = "Your circadian rhythm is trainable. Every morning you get up at the same time, the next morning gets easier. You're building a habit right now.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_40" = "Reach both arms above your head. Stretch as far as you can. Hold for 5 seconds. Blood flows, muscles activate, alertness increases. Simple and effective.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_41" = "Early risers report higher life satisfaction, better mental health, and more productivity. The secret? They don't want to get up either. They just do.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_42" = "Each snooze cycle drops you into light sleep. You wake up mid-cycle feeling worse than before. Snoozing is scientifically counterproductive. Stop it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_43" = "Think of one thing—just one—that you're looking forward to today. A meal, a conversation, a task. Hold that thought. Now get up and go get it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_44" = "The version of you who set this alarm was thinking clearly. The version hitting snooze is running on impulse. Trust the clear-headed version.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_45" = "Wasting your morning is wasting your life in slow motion. You don't get mornings back. This one is happening right now. Don't let it pass unused.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_46" = "Your brain loses 1-2% of its water overnight. That dehydration causes brain fog and fatigue. A glass of water will wake you faster than coffee.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_47" = "Neck rolls, shoulder shrugs, toe touches. Three stretches, 30 seconds total. Your body goes from sleep mode to ready mode. That's your only task.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_48" = "Getting up when it's hard builds discipline that transfers to every area of your life. This small act of courage echoes through your entire day.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_49" = "Going from horizontal to vertical changes everything. Blood flow shifts, brain chemistry changes, alertness kicks in. Sit up first. The rest follows.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_50" = "You're not 'sleeping in.' You're choosing to delay your life. Every second past your alarm is a micro-decision to stay small. Choose big. Get up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_51" = "Excuses are loudest in the morning. They quiet down once you're standing. Rise before the excuses talk you out of it. Move first, think second.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_52" = "Your goals don't pause while you snooze. Time keeps moving. Your competition is already up. Your dreams require you to be awake. Get moving.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_53" = "Open a window. One breath of fresh air contains the oxygen your brain has been craving all night. Let the outside world wake you up naturally.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_54" = "Remember why you chose this time. A workout, a project, a peaceful morning. That reason hasn't changed just because you're sleepy. Honor it.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_55" = "Energy creates energy. The first step feels impossible, but movement generates momentum. Walk to the kitchen, start coffee, and energy follows.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_56" = "Today has something for you that yesterday didn't. A new chance, a new idea, a new connection. But you can't receive any of it from bed.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_57" = "Cold water on your wrists and face activates the dive reflex—heart rate drops, alertness spikes. It's the fastest natural wake-up method known.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_58" = "Your pillow whispers comfort, but it means stagnation. Five more minutes becomes fifty. You know this pattern. Break it right now. Stand up.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_59" = "Stand up. Once you're vertical, the hardest part is over. Your brain will catch up in 90 seconds. Just get your body upright first.";
"nudge_cant_wake_up_detail_60" = "This isn't a rehearsal. This is your actual life, happening right now. Every morning you waste is gone forever. Wake up to the life you want.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — self_loathing (15-60)
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_15" = "You are not your worst moment.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_16" = "Talk to yourself like someone you love.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_17" = "Shame is a liar. Don't believe it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_18" = "You showed up today. That's enough.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_19" = "Stop comparing your inside to their outside.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_20" = "You're allowed to be a work in progress.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_21" = "Name three things you did well this week.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_22" = "Your self-criticism isn't making you better.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_23" = "Imperfect action beats perfect paralysis.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_24" = "Would you say that to a friend?";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_25" = "You deserve your own kindness.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_26" = "Mistakes mean you're trying.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_27" = "Progress, not perfection.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_28" = "Your value isn't measured by productivity.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_29" = "You are enough right now.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_30" = "Self-hate is just a habit. Break it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_31" = "One kind thought about yourself. Right now.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_32" = "You don't need to earn rest.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_33" = "Your brain lies about you. Don't listen.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_34" = "Being hard on yourself isn't strength.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_35" = "Celebrate small wins. They matter.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_36" = "You survived every bad day so far.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_37" = "Self-compassion isn't weakness.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_38" = "Healing isn't linear. Bad days happen.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_39" = "Your inner critic needs a day off.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_40" = "You matter more than you know.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_41" = "Replace 'I should' with 'I could'.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_42" = "What went right today?";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_43" = "You're doing better than you think.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_44" = "Growth requires self-acceptance first.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_45" = "Forgive yourself like you'd forgive a child.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_46" = "The voice in your head isn't always right.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_47" = "You're not behind. You're on your path.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_48" = "Breathe. You're doing your best.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_49" = "Let go of who you think you should be.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_50" = "Your worth isn't up for debate.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_51" = "One thing you like about yourself. Go.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_52" = "Nobody has it all figured out.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_53" = "Rest is part of the work.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_54" = "Be as patient with yourself as with others.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_55" = "You're human. Humans are messy. That's okay.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_56" = "Stop punishing yourself for being imperfect.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_57" = "Your past doesn't define your future.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_58" = "Place your hand on your heart. Breathe.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_59" = "You're worthy of love, including your own.";
"nudge_self_loathing_notification_60" = "Today is a new start. Accept it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_15" = "You are not defined by one bad day, one mistake, or one failure. Your identity is the sum of thousands of moments. Most of them were fine. Remember that.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_16" = "If your best friend made the same mistake, would you call them worthless? No. Give yourself the same grace. Say something kind to yourself out loud. Now.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_17" = "Shame says you ARE bad. Guilt says you DID something bad. One is a lie, one is growth. Replace 'I'm terrible' with 'I made a mistake and I can learn.'";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_18" = "You woke up, faced the day, and made it this far. That takes more strength than you give yourself credit for. Acknowledge the effort.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_19" = "Social media shows highlight reels. You're comparing your behind-the-scenes to their best moments. It's not a fair comparison. Stop making it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_20" = "You don't need to have it all figured out. Nobody does. Being in progress means you're moving forward. That's more than enough.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_21" = "Write down three things you did well this week. Not big things—small ones count. Made your bed? Drank water? Showed up? Those are wins.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_22" = "Self-criticism activates your threat system, flooding you with cortisol. Self-compassion activates your care system. Choose the one that actually helps.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_23" = "Waiting to feel ready means waiting forever. Do something imperfectly today. Action creates confidence, not the other way around.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_24" = "Listen to what you just said about yourself. Now imagine saying it to someone you love. Feels cruel, right? Stop being cruel to yourself.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_25" = "You spend energy being kind to others all day. Save some for yourself. One kind thought: 'I'm doing my best and that matters.'";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_26" = "Mistakes are proof that you're trying. The only people who never fail are the ones who never attempt anything. Your failures are evidence of courage.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_27" = "Perfection is a moving target—you'll never reach it. Progress is real and measurable. Look back one month. See how far you've come.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_28" = "Your value as a person has nothing to do with what you produced today. You are valuable because you exist. Full stop. No conditions.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_29" = "You don't need to earn the right to exist. You don't need to prove your worth. You are enough, exactly as you are, right now. Believe it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_30" = "Self-hate is a neural pathway that strengthened through repetition. You can weaken it the same way—by choosing a different thought, again and again.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_31" = "Right now, think one kind thing about yourself. 'I have good taste.' 'I care about people.' 'I'm trying.' Whatever it is, hold it for 10 seconds.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_32" = "Rest is not a reward for being productive. It's a basic need, like water and food. You deserve rest simply because you're alive.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_33" = "Your brain has a negativity bias—it's wired to remember criticism and forget praise. Your negative self-talk is a bug, not a feature. Override it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_34" = "Harsh self-criticism doesn't motivate—it paralyzes. Research shows self-compassion leads to more resilience and better outcomes. Be firm but kind.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_35" = "Did you drink water today? Did you get dressed? Did you try? Those count. Small wins build momentum. Celebrate the tiny victories.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_36" = "Look at your track record: 100% survival rate for bad days. You've gotten through every single one. This one is no different.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_37" = "Self-compassion isn't letting yourself off the hook. It's saying 'I can do better' without saying 'I'm worthless.' It's the stronger stance.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_38" = "Some days are two steps forward, one step back. That's still one step forward. Healing isn't linear, and bad days don't erase good progress.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_39" = "Your inner critic has been working overtime. Give it the day off. For the next hour, catch every negative thought and replace it with neutral.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_40" = "People care about you more than you realize. Your existence matters to someone right now. You impact lives just by being here.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_41" = "'I should have done better' becomes 'I could do it differently next time.' Same message, zero shame. Language shapes feelings. Choose better words.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_42" = "Before bed, name one thing that went right today. Not what went wrong—what went right. Train your brain to notice the good. It's a skill.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_43" = "You're more capable than your anxiety tells you. You've handled difficult situations before. You'll handle this one too. Trust your track record.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_44" = "You can't hate yourself into a better version. Growth starts with accepting where you are. Acceptance isn't giving up—it's honest starting ground.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_45" = "A child who makes a mess doesn't deserve contempt. They deserve guidance. Treat yourself the same way. Be the wise, kind parent to yourself.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_46" = "Thoughts are not facts. 'I'm worthless' is a thought, not a truth. Challenge it: What's the evidence? Would a jury convict based on this?";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_47" = "There's no universal timeline for success, healing, or growth. Your path is yours. Comparing your chapter 3 to someone else's chapter 20 is unfair.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_48" = "Take a slow breath in for 4 counts. Hold for 4. Out for 4. Repeat. You're here. You're breathing. That's not nothing. That's everything.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_49" = "The gap between who you are and who you think you should be causes suffering. Close the gap by adjusting expectations, not by hating yourself harder.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_50" = "Your worth is not a variable. It doesn't increase when you succeed or decrease when you fail. It's constant. It's inherent. It's yours.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_51" = "Say one thing you like about yourself out loud. Your voice. Your loyalty. Your humor. Anything. Hearing yourself say it makes it real.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_52" = "Everyone is figuring it out as they go. The confident people you admire have the same doubts. The difference is they don't let doubt stop them.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_53" = "Rest isn't earned through exhaustion. It's scheduled through wisdom. Give yourself permission to pause without guilt. You need it. Take it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_54" = "You give others the benefit of the doubt. You forgive friends quickly. You understand when someone is struggling. Turn that same empathy inward.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_55" = "Humans are beautifully imperfect. Your quirks, your mistakes, your rough edges—they're part of being alive. Embrace the mess.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_56" = "Punishing yourself for being imperfect hasn't made you perfect. It's just made you miserable. Try a different approach: acceptance and gentle effort.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_57" = "Your past contains mistakes. So does everyone's. Those mistakes don't own your future unless you let them. Release them. Walk forward.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_58" = "Place your hand on your heart. Feel it beating. That heart has kept you alive through everything. It deserves your kindness. Give it.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_59" = "You are worthy of love—from others and from yourself. That worthiness isn't conditional. It doesn't depend on achievement. It just is.";
"nudge_self_loathing_detail_60" = "Right now is a fresh start. Not tomorrow, not Monday, not next year. Right now. Take a breath and begin again, with kindness as your guide.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — rumination (15-60)
"nudge_rumination_notification_15" = "That thought loop isn't helping.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_16" = "Get out of your head. Into your body.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_17" = "You've thought about this enough.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_18" = "Worrying is praying for what you don't want.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_19" = "Name 5 things you can see right now.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_20" = "Your thoughts are clouds. Let them pass.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_21" = "Overthinking won't change the outcome.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_22" = "Action is the antidote to anxiety.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_23" = "This moment is all that's real.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_24" = "Your brain is stuck in a loop. Break it.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_25" = "Notice your feet on the ground.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_26" = "Replaying the past changes nothing.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_27" = "What can you control right now?";
"nudge_rumination_notification_28" = "Breathe in for 4. Out for 8.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_29" = "You're safe in this exact moment.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_30" = "Write it down. Get it out of your head.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_31" = "Thinking about it more won't solve it.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_32" = "Move your body. Free your mind.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_33" = "The answer won't come from worrying.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_34" = "Come back to now. Where are you?";
"nudge_rumination_notification_35" = "Your mind is a bad neighborhood. Don't go alone.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_36" = "Put the thought on a shelf. Come back later.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_37" = "Is this thought useful or just familiar?";
"nudge_rumination_notification_38" = "Feel your hands. Wiggle your fingers.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_39" = "You don't have to solve everything today.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_40" = "That thought isn't a fact. It's a story.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_41" = "Splash cold water on your face.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_42" = "What would calm you advise worried you?";
"nudge_rumination_notification_43" = "You've survived 100% of your worst days.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_44" = "Clench your fists. Release. Feel the difference.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_45" = "Tomorrow's problems belong to tomorrow.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_46" = "Hum a song. Break the pattern.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_47" = "One step at a time is still moving.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_48" = "Your brain needs a task, not a worry.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_49" = "Look up. The sky is still there.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_50" = "Talk to someone. Thoughts shrink when shared.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_51" = "Hold an ice cube. Focus on the cold.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_52" = "Worrying and solving are different things.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_53" = "What would you tell a friend right now?";
"nudge_rumination_notification_54" = "Stretch. Touch your toes. Come back.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_55" = "The present is the only real thing.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_56" = "Stop rehearsing disasters.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_57" = "Count backwards from 100 by 7s.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_58" = "Go outside. Change the scenery.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_59" = "Name the feeling. That weakens it.";
"nudge_rumination_notification_60" = "You are not your thoughts.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_15" = "You've been going around this thought for a while now. Has it produced a solution? No. That's because rumination isn't problem-solving. It's spinning. Stop.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_16" = "Your body is your anchor to reality. Stand up, stretch your arms overhead, roll your neck. Physical sensation pulls you out of mental loops. Do it now.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_17" = "You've given this thought plenty of attention. More thinking won't reveal a new answer. Write your concern on paper, close the notebook, and move on.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_18" = "Worry is your brain rehearsing worst cases. But rehearsing doesn't prepare you—it exhausts you. Redirect that energy to one concrete action you can take now.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_19" = "Look around. Name 5 things you can see, 4 you can touch, 3 you can hear, 2 you can smell, 1 you can taste. This 5-4-3-2-1 grounds you in reality.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_20" = "Thoughts come and go like clouds. You don't need to grab every one. Watch the thought, label it 'thinking,' and let it float away. It has no power unless you hold it.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_21" = "Overthinking creates the illusion of productivity. You feel busy but produce nothing. The outcome doesn't change no matter how many times you replay it.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_22" = "Anxiety wants you to think more. But the cure is action. Pick the smallest possible next step and do it. Movement breaks the cycle.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_23" = "The past is gone. The future isn't here. This moment—right now—is the only place where life happens. Come back to it. What are you doing right now?";
"nudge_rumination_detail_24" = "Your brain has a glitch: it thinks repetitive thinking is useful. It's not. Recognize the loop, name it 'rumination,' and consciously redirect to a task.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_25" = "Press your feet firmly into the ground. Feel the pressure, the texture, the temperature. This is real. The thoughts are projections. Come back to what's solid.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_26" = "Replaying a conversation won't change what was said. Reimagining a scenario won't alter the outcome. The past is fixed. Your energy belongs to the present.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_27" = "Make two lists: 'Things I can control' and 'Things I can't.' Cross out the second list. Focus only on the first. This is where your power lives.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_28" = "Breathe in through your nose for 4 seconds. Out through your mouth for 8 seconds. The extended exhale activates your vagus nerve and calms your nervous system.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_29" = "Right now, in this exact second, you are safe. Your brain is projecting danger that isn't here. Come back to this moment. Nothing bad is happening now.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_30" = "Transfer the thought from your head to paper. Write it down, messy and unfiltered. Once it's on paper, your brain can let go. It's been captured.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_31" = "If 30 minutes of thinking didn't solve it, 30 more won't either. Set a timer for 5 minutes of focused problem-solving, then stop. Move to something else.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_32" = "Walk, stretch, do jumping jacks, dance—any physical movement forces your brain to shift resources from worry to coordination. Your body is the escape hatch.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_33" = "Worry pretends to be problem-solving, but it never produces solutions. Real solutions come from calm, focused thinking. First, calm down. Then think clearly.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_34" = "Where are you right now? What room? What's the temperature? What sounds do you hear? Describe your environment. This is called grounding. It works.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_35" = "Your mind left unsupervised goes to dark places. Don't go alone—talk to someone, journal, or use this moment to redirect. You're the supervisor.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_36" = "Imagine placing the worry on a shelf. You can come back to it later if you need to. But right now, it stays on the shelf. You have other things to do.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_37" = "Some thoughts feel true just because they're familiar. Ask: Is this thought useful? Does it help me act? If not, it's just noise. Let it go.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_38" = "Feel your hands. Clench them. Relax them. Wiggle each finger one at a time. This micro-movement redirects your brain from abstract worry to concrete sensation.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_39" = "You don't need to solve every problem today. Some problems solve themselves with time. Give yourself permission to leave this one for tomorrow.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_40" = "'I'm not good enough' is a thought, not a court ruling. Thoughts aren't facts. They're sentences your brain generates. You can choose which ones to believe.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_41" = "Splash cold water on your face. The cold triggers your dive reflex, slowing your heart rate and pulling your attention to the physical sensation. Reset.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_42" = "Imagine your calmest, wisest self giving advice to your worried self. What would they say? Probably something like: 'It'll be okay. Let it go.'";
"nudge_rumination_detail_43" = "Your track record for surviving difficult situations is 100%. Not one bad day has ended you. This one won't either. Let that evidence calm you.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_44" = "Clench both fists as tight as you can for 5 seconds. Now release. Feel the tension drain from your hands. That release feeling? Spread it to your whole body.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_45" = "Tomorrow has its own problems and its own solutions. Trying to solve tomorrow's issues today is like fighting ghosts. Put your energy where it's useful: now.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_46" = "Hum any song for 30 seconds. Humming activates your vagus nerve and forces your brain to switch from worry mode to auditory processing. Simple but effective.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_47" = "You don't need to leap to the finish line. Just take one small step forward. Progress, however small, breaks the paralysis of overthinking.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_48" = "An idle brain ruminates. A busy brain works. Give your brain a task—count tiles, name countries, recite lyrics. Anything is better than the worry loop.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_49" = "Tilt your head up and look at the sky or ceiling. Change your visual field. Looking up physically shifts your brain state from internal to external focus.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_50" = "Worries grow in silence. Say what you're thinking out loud to someone—or even to yourself. Hearing it externalized often reveals how overblown it is.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_51" = "Hold an ice cube in your hand. Focus entirely on the sensation—the cold, the melting, the dripping. This intense physical input overrides the mental loop.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_52" = "Worrying feels productive but isn't. Solving feels uncomfortable but is. Ask: Am I solving or worrying? If worrying, stop and either solve or let go.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_53" = "If a friend came to you with this exact worry, you'd tell them it'll be fine. Trust the advice you'd give others. Apply it to yourself.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_54" = "Stand up. Bend forward and touch your toes (or as close as you can). Hold for 10 seconds. The blood flow to your head and the stretch reset your mental state.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_55" = "The past is memory. The future is imagination. Only the present is real. Come back to what's real. What are you touching right now? Start there.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_56" = "Your brain is running a disaster movie on repeat. But you're not in a movie—you're in real life, where things are usually much more boring and much more okay.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_57" = "100, 93, 86, 79... Counting backwards by 7s requires just enough concentration to interrupt rumination without being stressful. Try it for 30 seconds.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_58" = "A change of environment changes your mental state. Walk outside, go to a different room, or just stand by a window. New input, new thoughts.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_59" = "Name the feeling: 'I'm anxious.' 'I'm frustrated.' Research shows that labeling emotions reduces their intensity. Name it to tame it.";
"nudge_rumination_detail_60" = "You have thoughts, but you are not your thoughts. You are the awareness that notices them. Step back. Observe the thought. You're bigger than it.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — procrastination (15-60)
"nudge_procrastination_notification_15" = "Start before you're ready.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_16" = "The task won't do itself.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_17" = "Two minutes. That's all you need.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_18" = "Perfectionism is procrastination in disguise.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_19" = "Done is better than perfect.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_20" = "You don't need motivation. You need action.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_21" = "What's one tiny step you can take now?";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_22" = "The hardest part is opening the file.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_23" = "Future you is begging present you to start.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_24" = "Avoidance feels good now, terrible later.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_25" = "Just show up. Quality comes later.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_26" = "You know what to do. Do it.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_27" = "Momentum starts with a single action.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_28" = "Stop planning. Start doing.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_29" = "The anxiety of not doing is worse than doing.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_30" = "Eat the frog. Do the hard thing first.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_31" = "5 minutes. Set a timer. Go.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_32" = "Action creates motivation, not the reverse.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_33" = "What are you avoiding? Face it.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_34" = "Every minute delayed is a minute lost.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_35" = "You're not lazy. You're scared. Start anyway.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_36" = "Break it into pieces. Do one piece.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_37" = "Resistance is strongest before you begin.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_38" = "Your excuses are creative. Use that energy to work.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_39" = "Ship it imperfect. Iterate later.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_40" = "The gap between where you are and want to be? Action.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_41" = "Procrastination is a debt with interest.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_42" = "Close all tabs. Open one thing. Work.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_43" = "You'll feel relieved the moment you start.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_44" = "Discipline beats motivation every time.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_45" = "One task. Full focus. 25 minutes. Go.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_46" = "Your comfort zone is shrinking your life.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_47" = "Stop researching. Start executing.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_48" = "Do the thing your future self will thank you for.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_49" = "Imperfect action now > perfect action never.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_50" = "The best time was yesterday. The second best is now.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_51" = "Put your phone down and start.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_52" = "What's the worst that happens if you try?";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_53" = "Progress > perfection. Always.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_54" = "Waiting for inspiration is procrastination.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_55" = "You've wasted enough time thinking about it.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_56" = "The task takes less time than you think.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_57" = "Begin. The rest will follow.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_58" = "Choose discomfort now or regret later.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_59" = "Three deep breaths. Then start.";
"nudge_procrastination_notification_60" = "Right now. Not later. Now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_15" = "Waiting until you feel ready is a trap. Readiness comes from doing, not waiting. Open the task, set a 2-minute timer, and just begin. Momentum follows.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_16" = "The task is sitting there getting heavier with every minute you avoid it. It won't shrink or disappear. But the relief of starting is immediate.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_17" = "The 2-minute rule: if it takes less than 2 minutes, do it now. If it takes more, commit to just 2 minutes of it. You'll often continue beyond that.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_18" = "Perfectionism tells you it has to be perfect to be worth doing. That's a lie. A finished draft beats an imagined masterpiece every single time.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_19" = "Version one doesn't need to be good. It needs to exist. Create the ugly first version. You can improve it later. But you can't improve nothing.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_20" = "Motivation follows action, not the other way around. You won't feel like doing it until you start doing it. Start, and the feeling will come.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_21" = "What's the tiniest possible step? Not 'write the report' but 'open the document.' Not 'clean the house' but 'pick up one thing.' Do that step now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_22" = "The biggest barrier is starting. Once the file is open, the cursor is blinking, and you've typed one word, the resistance drops. Get past the first click.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_23" = "Imagine yourself tonight, having done the task. Relieved, proud, free. Now imagine yourself tonight, having put it off again. Anxious, guilty, stressed. Choose.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_24" = "Avoidance provides instant relief but long-term anxiety. Action provides instant discomfort but long-term peace. Which investment do you want to make?";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_25" = "Don't aim for a great first session. Aim for showing up. Quality improves with repetition. Today, just show up. Tomorrow, show up again.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_26" = "You know exactly what needs to be done. The plan is clear, the steps are clear. The only missing piece is action. Stop thinking. Start doing.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_27" = "A body in motion stays in motion. Take one action—any action—related to your task. Send one email, write one sentence, make one call. Momentum builds.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_28" = "Planning feels productive but can become a form of procrastination. You've planned enough. The plan is good enough. Execute. Now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_29" = "The anxiety you feel about the undone task is often worse than the task itself. Starting eliminates the anxiety. The task is usually easier than the worry.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_30" = "Mark Twain said eat the frog first thing in the morning. Your frog is the thing you're avoiding most. Do it first. Everything after feels easy.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_31" = "Set a timer for 5 minutes. Work with full focus until it rings. When it rings, you can stop if you want. But you probably won't want to.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_32" = "You're waiting to feel motivated. But motivation is a result of action, not a prerequisite. Start working, and motivation will arrive uninvited.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_33" = "Name the task you're avoiding. Say it out loud. Now ask: what specifically about it scares you? Name the fear. Named fears lose their power.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_34" = "Every minute you delay, the task gets psychologically heavier. The actual work stays the same, but the dread compounds. Cut the dread by starting now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_35" = "Procrastination isn't laziness—it's fear of failure, judgment, or discomfort. You're not lazy. You're avoiding pain. But starting is less painful than avoiding.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_36" = "Don't look at the whole mountain. Look at the next step. Break the task into 5-minute chunks. Do one chunk. Then decide about the next. Small bites only.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_37" = "Resistance is loudest right before you begin. It's your brain's last attempt to keep you comfortable. Push through the first 60 seconds and it fades.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_38" = "You spend more energy avoiding the task than doing it. All that creative excuse-making? Channel it into the actual work. You have the energy. Use it.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_39" = "Don't polish. Ship. The world rewards done, not perfect. Get version 1 out the door. You can iterate later with real feedback instead of imagined criticism.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_40" = "The distance between your current life and the life you want is filled with tasks you keep putting off. Each completed task moves you forward. Do one now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_41" = "Procrastination charges interest: stress, guilt, rushed work, missed opportunities. The longer you wait, the more you pay. Settle the debt. Start now.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_42" = "Digital distraction enables procrastination. Close all browser tabs, put your phone in another room, and open only the one thing you need. Environment wins.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_43" = "Notice how good it feels when you finally start something you've been putting off. That relief is available right now. All you have to do is begin.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_44" = "Motivation is unreliable. It comes and goes like weather. Discipline is a skill you build. Show up regardless of how you feel. That's the real superpower.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_45" = "The Pomodoro technique: 25 minutes of focused work, 5-minute break. Just one Pomodoro. That's all you need to commit to right now. Set the timer and go.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_46" = "Your comfort zone feels safe, but it's actually shrinking your potential every day you stay in it. Growth happens at the edges. Step out. Just one step.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_47" = "You've read enough articles, watched enough videos, and gathered enough information. Knowledge without action is entertainment, not progress. Execute.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_48" = "10 years from now, you'll wish you had started today. You can't go back in time, but you can start right now. Make future you grateful.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_49" = "An imperfect attempt teaches you more than a perfect plan. Action produces feedback. Feedback produces improvement. But it all starts with action.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_50" = "The second best time to start is right now. You can't change yesterday. But right now, in this moment, you have the power to begin. Use it.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_51" = "Your phone is the #1 procrastination tool ever invented. Put it face down in another room. Remove the distraction and the task becomes surprisingly doable.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_52" = "What's the actual worst case? Usually it's 'I try and it's not great.' That's not a catastrophe—that's learning. The real worst case is never trying.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_53" = "Progress compounds. Each small step forward makes the next step easier. Perfection doesn't compound—it paralyzes. Choose progress, always.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_54" = "Waiting for the right moment, the right mood, or the right inspiration is just procrastination wearing a disguise. The right moment is now. Start.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_55" = "Count how many hours you've spent thinking about this task versus doing it. The thinking-to-doing ratio is probably embarrassing. Flip it. Do more, think less.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_56" = "Most tasks take 20-50% less time than you estimate. Your brain inflates the difficulty to justify avoidance. Start, and discover how manageable it actually is.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_57" = "Don't wait for a perfect beginning. Begin imperfectly. The first word doesn't need to be eloquent. The first step doesn't need to be graceful. Just begin.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_58" = "You can choose: short-term discomfort of doing the work now, or long-term discomfort of carrying it as unfinished weight. One choice frees you. Make it.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_59" = "Take three slow breaths to clear the resistance. Then open the task and work for exactly 90 seconds. Not 5 minutes—90 seconds. That's your only commitment.";
"nudge_procrastination_detail_60" = "This is the moment. Not in an hour, not after lunch, not tomorrow morning. Right now. The task is waiting. You're ready. Go.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — anxiety (15-60)
"nudge_anxiety_notification_15" = "Anxiety is future-tripping. Come back.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_16" = "Your body is safe. Tell it.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_17" = "Exhale longer than you inhale.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_18" = "This feeling will pass. It always does.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_19" = "Ground yourself. 5 things you see.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_20" = "You don't have to figure it out right now.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_21" = "Place your hand on your chest. Breathe.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_22" = "Anxiety lies about the odds.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_23" = "What's true right now? Not what might be.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_24" = "Your nervous system needs a reset. Breathe.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_25" = "You've handled hard things before.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_26" = "Name the fear. Watch it shrink.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_27" = "Tense your whole body. Now release.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_28" = "One worry at a time. Not all at once.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_29" = "The worst case rarely happens.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_30" = "Your thoughts are not predictions.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_31" = "Slow down. There's no emergency.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_32" = "Feel your feet. You're on solid ground.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_33" = "Anxiety is a wave. Let it crest and pass.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_34" = "You're stronger than this feeling.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_35" = "Cold water on wrists. Instant calm.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_36" = "Take up space. Uncross your arms.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_37" = "What can you do right now? Focus on that.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_38" = "Your breath is your remote control. Use it.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_39" = "Nothing is as urgent as anxiety claims.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_40" = "Put both feet flat on the floor.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_41" = "You're having a thought, not a crisis.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_42" = "Hum. It activates your vagus nerve.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_43" = "This too shall pass.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_44" = "Step outside. Fresh air helps.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_45" = "What would 80-year-old you say about this?";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_46" = "Box breathing: 4 in, 4 hold, 4 out, 4 hold.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_47" = "Anxiety makes everything seem urgent. It's not.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_48" = "You're safe. Right here, right now.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_49" = "Shake your hands for 10 seconds.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_50" = "The feeling is temporary. You are permanent.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_51" = "Notice the anxiety. Don't become it.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_52" = "Drink cold water slowly.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_53" = "What's going right? List three things.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_54" = "Unclench your jaw. Drop your shoulders.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_55" = "You are not in danger. Just uncomfortable.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_56" = "Press your palms together. Feel the pressure.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_57" = "This moment is manageable. Stay in it.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_58" = "Breathe like you're fogging up a mirror.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_59" = "Your brain is a smoke alarm. Not a fire.";
"nudge_anxiety_notification_60" = "Gentle reminder: you're going to be okay.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_15" = "Anxiety transports you to a future that doesn't exist yet. Right now, in this moment, you're fine. Come back to the present. What are you touching right now?";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_16" = "Your body can't distinguish between real danger and imagined danger. Tell it explicitly: 'I am safe.' Place your hand on your chest and say it aloud.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_17" = "Breathe in for 4 counts. Out for 8 counts. The long exhale activates your parasympathetic nervous system—your body's built-in calm-down switch.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_18" = "Every anxious feeling you've ever had has eventually passed. This one will too. You don't need to fight it. Just wait it out. It's temporary.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_19" = "5-4-3-2-1 grounding: Name 5 things you see, 4 you can touch, 3 you hear, 2 you smell, 1 you taste. This pulls your brain from anxiety to reality.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_20" = "You don't need all the answers right now. Some things resolve themselves with time. Give yourself permission to not know, and let that be okay for today.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_21" = "Physical touch calms the nervous system. Place your hand on your chest, feel your heartbeat, and breathe slowly. You're here. You're alive. That's enough.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_22" = "Anxiety inflates the probability of bad outcomes and shrinks the probability of good ones. The math is wrong. Most things you worry about never happen.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_23" = "Separate facts from fears. What is actually true right now? Not what might happen, not what could go wrong—what is real in this moment? Usually, you're fine.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_24" = "Your nervous system is stuck in fight-or-flight. Reset it: breathe in for 4, hold for 7, out for 8. Three rounds. Your heart rate will drop noticeably.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_25" = "Look at your history. You've faced difficult moments and survived all of them. Your track record is perfect. This challenge is no different.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_26" = "Vague fear is the worst kind. Name it specifically: 'I'm afraid of failing the exam.' Named fears are smaller than unnamed ones. Name it right now.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_27" = "Progressive muscle relaxation: Tense every muscle in your body for 5 seconds—face, shoulders, arms, core, legs. Now release all at once. Feel the difference.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_28" = "You're trying to solve ten problems at once. Pick one. Just one. Set the others aside. One worry at a time is manageable. All at once is overwhelming.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_29" = "Studies show 85% of things people worry about never happen. Of the 15% that do, 79% are handled better than expected. The odds are in your favor.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_30" = "Anxious thoughts feel like predictions, but they're just guesses. Bad guesses. Your brain is not a fortune teller. It's a worry machine. Don't trust it blindly.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_31" = "Is there an actual emergency right now? No? Then slow down. Walk slower, talk slower, breathe slower. Your pace tells your brain how urgent things are.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_32" = "Your feet are on the ground. Feel them. Press them down. The earth is solid beneath you. You are supported. You are stable. Breathe from that place.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_33" = "Anxiety is like a wave—it rises, peaks, and falls. You can't stop the wave, but you can ride it. Stay with the sensation. It will crest and pass.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_34" = "You've endured worse than this and come through. This feeling, while uncomfortable, is not a threat. You are stronger than the anxiety wants you to believe.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_35" = "Run cold water over your wrists for 30 seconds. The cold constricts blood vessels and triggers a calming reflex. Simple, physical, effective.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_36" = "Anxious bodies curl inward. Counteract it: stand tall, uncross your arms, take up space. Open posture sends a safety signal to your brain.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_37" = "Instead of focusing on everything that could go wrong, ask: what can I do right now? One small action beats an hour of worrying. Act on what's in your control.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_38" = "Your breath controls your nervous system more than anything else. Slow it down: 4 counts in, 6 counts out. Do this for 2 minutes. You'll feel the shift.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_39" = "Anxiety creates false urgency. Very few things need to be decided or done right this second. Give yourself space. Most things can wait an hour or a day.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_40" = "Press both feet flat on the floor. Feel the weight of your body. You are here. Not in the scary future. Here. This is the only moment that needs your attention.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_41" = "You're having an anxious thought, not a crisis. There's a difference. The thought is uncomfortable but not dangerous. Observe it like a passing car.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_42" = "Humming for 30 seconds stimulates your vagus nerve, which directly lowers heart rate and anxiety. Try it: hum any note. Feel the vibration in your chest.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_43" = "This shall pass. It always has, and it always will. Hold on. Breathe. The feeling is intense but temporary. You are the constant. Not the anxiety.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_44" = "Step outside, even for 60 seconds. Nature, fresh air, and a change of scenery all reduce cortisol. You don't need to go far. Just go.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_45" = "Fast-forward to 80 years old. Will this matter? Probably not. Most of what we worry about is forgotten within weeks. Zoom out and see the bigger picture.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_46" = "Box breathing: Inhale 4 seconds. Hold 4 seconds. Exhale 4 seconds. Hold 4 seconds. Navy SEALs use this under extreme stress. It works. Do 4 rounds.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_47" = "Anxiety disguises preferences as emergencies. 'I must respond now.' 'I need to decide today.' Question the urgency. Is it real, or is anxiety talking?";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_48" = "In this exact second, nothing bad is happening to you. You are physically safe. Anxiety projects danger that isn't here. Come back to where you are.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_49" = "Shake your hands rapidly for 10 seconds, like you're flicking water off them. This simple movement releases tension stored in your nervous system.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_50" = "The anxious feeling will pass. It has a beginning, a middle, and an end. You are permanent. Anxiety is a visitor. Let it visit and leave.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_51" = "You can notice anxiety without becoming it. Say: 'I notice I'm feeling anxious.' That small distance between you and the feeling changes everything.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_52" = "Slowly drink a glass of cold water. Focus on the temperature, the swallowing, the sensation. This simple act engages your body and quiets your mind.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_53" = "Anxiety narrows your focus to what's wrong. Counterbalance: list three things going right. Your health, a relationship, a roof overhead. Broaden the view.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_54" = "Body scan: Unclench your jaw. Drop your shoulders away from your ears. Unfurrow your brow. Relax your hands. You were holding tension you didn't know about.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_55" = "Discomfort and danger are not the same thing. Anxiety feels dangerous but it's just uncomfortable. You can handle discomfort. You've done it your whole life.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_56" = "Press your palms together firmly for 10 seconds. Focus on the pressure, the warmth, the contact. This bilateral stimulation calms the amygdala.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_57" = "Don't try to solve everything at once. This moment is manageable. Just this one moment. Handle it, then handle the next. Moment by moment.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_58" = "Breathe out like you're fogging up a mirror—slow, warm, steady. This engages your diaphragm and signals your nervous system that you're safe.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_59" = "Your brain is sounding the alarm, but there's no fire. It's a false alarm. Acknowledge it, don't panic about the panic, and let the alarm turn off.";
"nudge_anxiety_detail_60" = "You are going to be okay. Not because nothing bad will ever happen, but because you have the strength and resources to handle whatever comes. Trust yourself.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — lying (15-60)
"nudge_lying_notification_15" = "Truth is lighter than lies.";
"nudge_lying_notification_16" = "Every lie needs a lie to support it.";
"nudge_lying_notification_17" = "Honesty is a gift to yourself.";
"nudge_lying_notification_18" = "Who are you when no one is watching?";
"nudge_lying_notification_19" = "Trust is built one truth at a time.";
"nudge_lying_notification_20" = "Small lies erode big relationships.";
"nudge_lying_notification_21" = "Be the person who doesn't need to lie.";
"nudge_lying_notification_22" = "How much energy does hiding take?";
"nudge_lying_notification_23" = "Integrity is what you do in the dark.";
"nudge_lying_notification_24" = "Can you get through today without a lie?";
"nudge_lying_notification_25" = "The truth may hurt briefly. Lies hurt forever.";
"nudge_lying_notification_26" = "Real relationships need real honesty.";
"nudge_lying_notification_27" = "Lying to yourself counts too.";
"nudge_lying_notification_28" = "Silence is better than a lie.";
"nudge_lying_notification_29" = "You're better than the easy way out.";
"nudge_lying_notification_30" = "What would an honest person do?";
"nudge_lying_notification_31" = "Honesty takes courage. You have it.";
"nudge_lying_notification_32" = "One honest conversation can change everything.";
"nudge_lying_notification_33" = "Lies make you smaller. Truth makes you free.";
"nudge_lying_notification_34" = "Are you being real right now?";
"nudge_lying_notification_35" = "Character is built in honest moments.";
"nudge_lying_notification_36" = "People respect honesty more than perfection.";
"nudge_lying_notification_37" = "What are you afraid to admit?";
"nudge_lying_notification_38" = "Honesty is the shortcut to peace.";
"nudge_lying_notification_39" = "Your word is your bond. Protect it.";
"nudge_lying_notification_40" = "Stop performing. Start being.";
"nudge_lying_notification_41" = "Vulnerability isn't weakness. It's strength.";
"nudge_lying_notification_42" = "The mask gets heavier every day.";
"nudge_lying_notification_43" = "An honest mistake beats a dishonest success.";
"nudge_lying_notification_44" = "Trust yourself enough to tell the truth.";
"nudge_lying_notification_45" = "Exaggeration is a form of lying.";
"nudge_lying_notification_46" = "Who could you be if you dropped the act?";
"nudge_lying_notification_47" = "Honesty simplifies everything.";
"nudge_lying_notification_48" = "Your lies don't protect anyone.";
"nudge_lying_notification_49" = "Say what you mean. Mean what you say.";
"nudge_lying_notification_50" = "Be someone others can trust.";
"nudge_lying_notification_51" = "Authenticity is attractive.";
"nudge_lying_notification_52" = "One truth today. Start small.";
"nudge_lying_notification_53" = "Lies build prisons. Truth opens doors.";
"nudge_lying_notification_54" = "If you have to lie about it, reconsider it.";
"nudge_lying_notification_55" = "The best liars fool themselves first.";
"nudge_lying_notification_56" = "Is this who you want to be?";
"nudge_lying_notification_57" = "Freedom starts with honest words.";
"nudge_lying_notification_58" = "Every lie distances you from yourself.";
"nudge_lying_notification_59" = "Practice radical honesty today.";
"nudge_lying_notification_60" = "Speak truth. Even when your voice shakes.";
"nudge_lying_detail_15" = "Lies create mental weight. Every lie you tell requires memory, maintenance, and worry about being caught. Truth is simple. It doesn't need a filing system.";
"nudge_lying_detail_16" = "One lie leads to another. You lie to cover the first lie, then lie again to maintain consistency. The web gets tangled. Cut it now. Tell one truth today.";
"nudge_lying_detail_17" = "When you're honest, you don't need to manage stories or remember what you said to whom. Honesty is the ultimate simplification of your life.";
"nudge_lying_detail_18" = "Your true character is revealed when no one is watching. The gap between your public and private self is measured in lies. Close the gap.";
"nudge_lying_detail_19" = "Trust takes years to build and seconds to destroy. Each honest interaction is a brick. Each lie is a crack. Build something solid today.";
"nudge_lying_detail_20" = "Small lies feel harmless: 'I'm fine,' 'Traffic was bad,' 'I already ate.' But each one teaches you that truth is optional. It's not.";
"nudge_lying_detail_21" = "Imagine living a life where you never need to cover your tracks. Where every word matches reality. That life starts with your next sentence.";
"nudge_lying_detail_22" = "Maintaining lies consumes cognitive energy—energy you could use for creativity, connection, or peace. Calculate the real cost of dishonesty.";
"nudge_lying_detail_23" = "Integrity means your values, words, and actions align. When they don't, you feel the disconnect. That unease? It's your integrity asking to be restored.";
"nudge_lying_detail_24" = "Challenge yourself: go 24 hours without a single lie. Not even a white one. Notice how it feels. Notice how much easier conversations become.";
"nudge_lying_detail_25" = "A painful truth, delivered with kindness, heals faster than a comfortable lie that festers. The truth may sting, but lies rot.";
"nudge_lying_detail_26" = "Real connection requires real honesty. You can't be truly known while wearing a mask. Vulnerability—not perfection—is what bonds people.";
"nudge_lying_detail_27" = "The most dangerous lies are the ones you tell yourself. 'I can stop anytime.' 'It's not that bad.' 'I'll change later.' Be honest with yourself first.";
"nudge_lying_detail_28" = "Sometimes the bravest thing is saying nothing at all. If you can't tell the truth, don't fill the space with a lie. Silence has more integrity.";
"nudge_lying_detail_29" = "Lying is the easy path, but easy paths lead to hard lives. Hard paths—honesty, accountability, vulnerability—lead to easy lives. Choose the harder path.";
"nudge_lying_detail_30" = "Next time you're tempted to lie, pause and ask: 'What would an honest person do here?' Then do that. You become the person you consistently act as.";
"nudge_lying_detail_31" = "Telling the truth when it's hard is one of the most courageous things you can do. It takes more strength than any lie. That courage lives in you.";
"nudge_lying_detail_32" = "One honest conversation with someone you've been lying to can transform the relationship. It won't be comfortable. But it will be real. And real is better.";
"nudge_lying_detail_33" = "Each lie shrinks your self-respect. Each truth expands it. Over time, honest people develop an unshakeable sense of self. That's freedom.";
"nudge_lying_detail_34" = "Right now, in this moment, are you being completely real? With yourself? With others? Check in. If something feels off, honesty is the fix.";
"nudge_lying_detail_35" = "Your character isn't what you claim to be—it's what you do repeatedly. Choose honesty enough times and it becomes who you are.";
"nudge_lying_detail_36" = "People don't respect perfect people—they respect honest ones. Admitting a mistake earns more respect than any elaborate cover-up.";
"nudge_lying_detail_37" = "What's the thing you're afraid to say out loud? Write it down. You don't have to share it yet, but admitting it to yourself is step one.";
"nudge_lying_detail_38" = "Lies create anxiety. Truth creates peace. The discomfort of honesty lasts minutes. The anxiety of maintaining lies lasts indefinitely.";
"nudge_lying_detail_39" = "Your word is the only currency that never inflates. Every time you keep it, it increases in value. Every time you break it, it depreciates. Protect it.";
"nudge_lying_detail_40" = "Stop performing a version of yourself that doesn't exist. The real you—flawed, uncertain, genuine—is more worthy of connection than any performance.";
"nudge_lying_detail_41" = "Showing your real self feels risky. But vulnerability is the foundation of all deep relationships. People connect with real, not with polished.";
"nudge_lying_detail_42" = "Every mask you wear gets heavier with time. The energy spent maintaining false images could be spent building your real life. Take off one mask today.";
"nudge_lying_detail_43" = "An honest mistake shows character. A dishonest success reveals its absence. The world needs more people who own their failures. Be one of them.";
"nudge_lying_detail_44" = "Trust yourself to handle the consequences of truth. You're stronger than you think. The truth might be uncomfortable, but you can handle discomfort.";
"nudge_lying_detail_45" = "Exaggerating, omitting, and spinning are all forms of lying. Hold yourself to a higher standard. Say exactly what happened. No more, no less.";
"nudge_lying_detail_46" = "What if you stopped managing impressions and just... existed? The relief of authenticity is something no amount of successful lying can match.";
"nudge_lying_detail_47" = "Honesty eliminates the need to track stories, manage impressions, or worry about being caught. It's the most efficient way to live. Choose efficiency.";
"nudge_lying_detail_48" = "Your lies don't protect anyone—they protect your comfort. The people you lie to deserve better. Give them the respect of truth.";
"nudge_lying_detail_49" = "Mean what you say, say what you mean, and don't say it mean. Honesty and kindness aren't opposites. Practice both.";
"nudge_lying_detail_50" = "Being someone others can trust starts with being trustworthy in the smallest moments. Return the extra change. Admit the mistake. Keep the promise.";
"nudge_lying_detail_51" = "Authenticity is magnetic. People are drawn to those who are genuine. You don't need to be perfect to be attractive—you need to be real.";
"nudge_lying_detail_52" = "Start today with one small truth. Something you'd normally sugarcoat or skip over. Say it plainly. Notice how it feels. That feeling is integrity.";
"nudge_lying_detail_53" = "Lies build invisible prisons around your life. Each truth you tell removes a bar. Keep telling truths until you're completely free.";
"nudge_lying_detail_54" = "If an action requires lying to justify it, that's your answer. The need to lie is a signal that something is wrong. Listen to that signal.";
"nudge_lying_detail_55" = "The most skilled liars end up believing their own stories. That's the real danger—losing touch with reality. Stay grounded in truth.";
"nudge_lying_detail_56" = "Take 10 seconds and ask: Is this who I want to be? A person who hides, deflects, and deceives? Or someone who stands in truth? Choose right now.";
"nudge_lying_detail_57" = "Freedom isn't having the right to do whatever you want. It's living so transparently that you have nothing to hide. That's real freedom.";
"nudge_lying_detail_58" = "Every lie creates distance—between you and others, between you and yourself. Each truth closes that gap. Close the distance today.";
"nudge_lying_detail_59" = "Radical honesty means saying what's true, even when it's uncomfortable. Start with yourself. What's one thing you've been denying? Acknowledge it.";
"nudge_lying_detail_60" = "Speak your truth, even when your voice trembles. Courage isn't the absence of fear—it's acting honestly despite it. Today, choose courage.";

// MARK: - Nudge Expansion v1.8.0 — bad_mouthing (15-60)
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_15" = "Words have weight. Choose carefully.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_16" = "Gossip poisons the gossiper most.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_17" = "Would you say it to their face?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_18" = "Speak about people as if they're listening.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_19" = "Complaining doesn't change anything.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_20" = "If you can't help, don't harm.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_21" = "Your words reveal your character.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_22" = "Build people up, don't tear them down.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_23" = "Negativity is contagious. Don't spread it.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_24" = "Find something kind to say instead.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_25" = "Other people's flaws aren't your hobby.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_26" = "What you say about others says about you.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_27" = "Bite your tongue. Seriously.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_28" = "Replace criticism with curiosity.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_29" = "Everyone is fighting something invisible.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_30" = "Praise in public. Criticize in private.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_31" = "How would they feel hearing you right now?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_32" = "Gossip creates temporary connection but lasting damage.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_33" = "Strong people lift others. Weak people pull down.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_34" = "Before you speak: Is it true? Kind? Necessary?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_35" = "You don't know their whole story.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_36" = "Talking badly won't make you feel better.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_37" = "Redirect the conversation to something positive.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_38" = "Be the person who defends absent people.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_39" = "Bitterness is a poison you drink yourself.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_40" = "Focus on your own growth, not their flaws.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_41" = "Your tongue can build or destroy. Choose.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_42" = "Did someone bad-mouth you? Don't pass it on.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_43" = "Silence the critic. Awaken the encourager.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_44" = "Judgment creates distance. Empathy creates connection.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_45" = "Compliment someone today. Mean it.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_46" = "Your words plant seeds. Plant good ones.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_47" = "Think twice. Speak once.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_48" = "The urge to criticize usually reflects insecurity.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_49" = "Rise above the conversation.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_50" = "Choose to be a safe person.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_51" = "Your reputation is what you say about others.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_52" = "Break the cycle. Speak life.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_53" = "Compassion is always the right response.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_54" = "Who benefits from your harsh words?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_55" = "Catch yourself before you gossip.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_56" = "Leave people better than you found them.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_57" = "Kind words cost nothing but mean everything.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_58" = "You don't have to join the negativity.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_59" = "Every person is someone's whole world.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_notification_60" = "Speak with the kindness you'd want to receive.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_15" = "Words carry weight—once spoken, they can't be unsaid. Before criticizing someone, pause for 10 seconds. Is it worth it? Usually, it's not.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_16" = "Research shows gossip increases cortisol in the gossiper. You think you're venting, but you're actually stressing yourself out. It hurts you more than them.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_17" = "The test of integrity: would you say these exact words to their face? If not, don't say them behind their back. If yes, say it to them, not about them.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_18" = "Live as if every word you say about someone will be heard by them. Because it often is—the world is smaller than you think. Speak accordingly.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_19" = "Complaining about someone without talking to them is just theater. It changes nothing and damages trust. If there's a real issue, address it directly.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_20" = "The minimum standard: don't make things worse. If you can't build someone up right now, at least don't tear them down. Silence is an acceptable choice.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_21" = "Every harsh word you say about others reveals something about your own insecurities. Secure people don't need to diminish others. What does your speech reveal?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_22" = "Be the person in the room who finds something positive to say about everyone. That person earns deep trust because people know they're safe with you.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_23" = "Negative talk is contagious—one complaint invites another. You can also be the one who starts a positive chain. Change the energy by changing your words.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_24" = "Right now, think of one genuinely kind thing you could say about someone you usually criticize. Text it to them, or tell someone else. Replace the habit.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_25" = "Focusing on other people's flaws is a full-time hobby that produces nothing. Redirect that energy toward your own improvement. You'll be happier.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_26" = "People learn more about you from how you talk about others than from how you talk about yourself. Your words about absent people are your real résumé.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_27" = "Physically bite your tongue for 3 seconds before responding to the urge to criticize. That tiny pause creates space for a better choice. Use it.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_28" = "Instead of 'they're so annoying,' try 'I wonder why they do that.' Curiosity opens doors that criticism slams shut. Same situation, different approach.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_29" = "The person you're criticizing might be dealing with grief, illness, financial stress, or trauma you know nothing about. Grant them the grace you'd want.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_30" = "If someone needs correction, do it privately and respectfully. Public criticism humiliates. Private feedback helps. Be the person who chooses to help.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_31" = "Close your eyes and imagine the person hearing every word you're about to say. See their face. See their reaction. Still want to say it?";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_32" = "Gossip feels bonding in the moment—shared criticism creates a false sense of closeness. But it builds relationships on sand. Real bonds need real kindness.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_33" = "It takes zero strength to point out someone's flaws. It takes real strength to see their potential and encourage it. Be the stronger person.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_34" = "Three gates of speech: Is it true? Is it kind? Is it necessary? If it doesn't pass all three, don't let it past your lips.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_35" = "You're seeing a fraction of their life and judging the whole thing. You don't know their battles, their history, or their context. Assume good intent.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_36" = "After talking badly about someone, do you feel lighter? No—you feel guilty and small. The brief satisfaction is a lie. Kindness is the real relief.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_37" = "When a conversation turns negative, you can redirect it. 'Hey, have you heard about...' or 'Actually, I really like how they...' Be the redirect.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_38" = "Defending someone who isn't present is one of the most admirable things a person can do. It shows loyalty and character. Be that person.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_39" = "Bitterness toward others doesn't hurt them—they're probably not even aware. It hurts you. Every resentful thought is a drop of poison in your own cup.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_40" = "Time spent analyzing others' flaws is time not spent improving yourself. Every minute of gossip is a minute stolen from your own growth.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_41" = "Your tongue is powerful—it can encourage, heal, inspire, or it can wound, destroy, and poison. Which direction are you pointing it today? Choose build.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_42" = "If someone talked badly about you, it hurt. Don't pass that pain forward. Break the chain. Respond to negativity with silence or kindness.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_43" = "You have an inner critic and an inner encourager. The one you exercise gets stronger. Today, exercise the encourager. Find one good thing to say about someone.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_44" = "Judging creates walls between people. Empathy builds bridges. You don't have to agree with someone to understand them. Seek understanding first.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_45" = "Compliment someone genuinely today. Not flattery—real recognition. 'I noticed you did X well.' Watch how it transforms their day and yours.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_46" = "Every word is a seed—in someone else's mind and in your own. Plant words of encouragement, appreciation, and kindness. They'll grow into something beautiful.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_47" = "The two-thought rule: think about what you want to say. Then think about it again. If it still needs to be said after two rounds of thinking, say it kindly.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_48" = "When you feel the urge to criticize someone, ask: am I trying to help, or am I trying to feel superior? Honest answer usually reveals insecurity.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_49" = "You can leave a conversation that's turning into a gossip session. You can change the topic. You can stay silent. You always have a choice. Rise above.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_50" = "A safe person is someone others trust with their vulnerabilities. You become that by never weaponizing what people share and never talking behind backs.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_51" = "Your reputation is essentially what you say about others when they're not around. Build a reputation for kindness. It's the most valuable one you can have.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_52" = "Every negative cycle can be broken. Starting right now, choose to speak life—encouragement, praise, understanding. The cycle breaks the moment you decide.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_53" = "Compassion isn't about excusing bad behavior—it's about recognizing humanity in everyone. You can hold boundaries while still speaking with kindness.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_54" = "Who benefits when you say something harsh? Not the target. Not your listeners. Not you. Nobody benefits. So why say it? Choose differently.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_55" = "Notice the moment gossip bubbles up. That split-second awareness is your opportunity. Catch it, pause, redirect. The more you practice, the easier it gets.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_56" = "Aim to leave every person slightly better than you found them. A smile, a kind word, a moment of attention. Small deposits of goodness compound.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_57" = "Kind words cost you nothing but can mean everything to someone. They might be the only kind words that person hears today. Don't underestimate their power.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_58" = "When negative talk starts, you don't have to participate. A simple 'I'd rather not talk about them' is enough. It takes courage, but it commands respect.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_59" = "Remember: that person you're judging is someone's child, partner, or best friend. They're someone's whole world. Treat them with the respect that deserves.";
"nudge_bad_mouthing_detail_60" = "The golden rule applies to speech too: talk about others the way you'd want them to talk about you. Simple, powerful, and always the right choice.";

