"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_43" = "Is this aligned with your goals?";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_44" = "Shame fuels addiction. Self-compassion breaks it.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_45" = "One day at a time. Today, you win.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_46" = "Breathe through it. The urge will pass.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_47" = "Real connection > artificial stimulation.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_48" = "You're building something. Don't demolish it.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_49" = "The easy choice isn't the right choice.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_50" = "Delay the urge by 10 minutes. You can do that.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_51" = "Go outside. Sunlight kills cravings.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_52" = "Channel that energy into something productive.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_53" = "Your future self is counting on you.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_54" = "This is a test. Pass it.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_55" = "Drink a glass of cold water. Reset.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_56" = "You have the power to choose differently.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_57" = "The urge is a liar. The regret is real.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_58" = "Stand up and stretch. Change your state.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_59" = "Every 'no' makes the next one easier.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_notification_60" = "You are more than this habit.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_15" = "Urges feel permanent but they're biochemical events that peak and fade within 15-20 minutes. You don't need to act on them. Just outlast them.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_16" = "Your screen is the battlefield. Leave the battlefield. Walk to another room, go outside, or put your phone in a drawer. Distance is your strongest weapon.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_17" = "The craving says you can't resist. That's false. You've resisted before. Every time you chose differently, you proved the craving wrong. Prove it wrong again.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_18" = "Set a timer for 20 minutes and do something else—anything. Push-ups, a walk, washing dishes. When the timer rings, the urge will be significantly weaker.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_19" = "Ask yourself: Am I actually aroused, or am I bored, lonely, stressed, or tired? Often the urge masks a real need. Address the real need instead.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_20" = "Physical movement floods your brain with endorphins that compete with the craving. Do 30 jumping jacks, push-ups, or a brisk walk. Your body is your ally.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_21" = "Don't bargain with the urge. 'Just a peek' is the voice of addiction, not reason. There's no such thing as just a peek. Shut it down completely.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_22" = "Project forward: the 3 seconds of pleasure vs. the hours of shame and regret that follow. The math never works out. Choose the future over the moment.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_23" = "A slip doesn't erase progress. You haven't lost everything—you've lost one battle. Get up immediately. The streak is about trajectory, not perfection.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_24" = "Close every browser tab. Now close the browser. Now lock your phone and put it away. Each step increases the distance between you and the behavior.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_25" = "Boredom is one of the biggest triggers. Your brain seeks stimulation. Have a list ready: a book, a podcast, exercise, a call to a friend. Use it now.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_26" = "Your brain's reward system has been hijacked. It says you need this. You don't. It's a trained response, not a genuine need. Retrain it by saying no.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_27" = "A cold shower for 30-60 seconds resets your nervous system, kills the urge, and releases endorphins. It's uncomfortable but incredibly effective. Do it.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_28" = "Neuroplasticity works both ways. Every time you resist an urge, the neural pathways for the habit weaken. You're literally rewiring your brain right now.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_29" = "Close your eyes. Imagine the person you want to be in 5 years. Is this behavior part of that person's life? No. Then don't do it. Become that person now.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_30" = "Dopamine from this source leaves you emptier than before—it's a net negative. Real happiness comes from connection, achievement, and growth. Choose real.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_31" = "The best version of you doesn't do this. You know that. Step into that version right now. Not tomorrow, not after one more time. Right now.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_32" = "This behavior changes how you see people, how you connect, and how you love. Your relationships—present and future—deserve someone who chose differently.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_33" = "Your environment matters more than willpower. Leave the room where you're tempted. Change locations. Put obstacles between you and the behavior.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_34" = "Every streak has defining moments—times when giving in felt easier than holding on. This is one of those moments. What you do now defines the streak.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_35" = "Late night + alone + bored = the highest risk combination. Recognize the pattern. Have a plan: call someone, leave the house, or go to bed early.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_36" = "Look at how far you've come. Every day of resistance is a victory. Don't throw away accumulated wins for a moment of weakness. Keep building.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_37" = "Physical exertion is the fastest way to redirect sexual energy. Drop and do 20 push-ups right now. Your body will channel the energy differently.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_38" = "Urge surfing: Don't fight the urge or give in. Just observe it. Watch it rise, peak, and fall like a wave. You're the surfer, not the wave.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_39" = "Isolation feeds addiction. Connection breaks it. Call a friend, text someone, or go where people are. You don't have to talk about the urge—just connect.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_40" = "The craving is strongest at 10 minutes. After that, it weakens rapidly. You only need to survive 10 minutes of intensity. You can do anything for 10 minutes.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_41" = "Your brain formed these pathways over time and it takes time to rewire them. Each day without acting on the urge, the old pathways weaken. Be patient with yourself.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_42" = "Device in another room. Charger in the kitchen. No phone in the bedroom. These simple environmental changes remove 80% of temptation. Set up your wins.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_43" = "Before acting, ask: Does this align with who I want to be? With my goals? With my values? If the answer is no, you have your answer. Act on your values.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_44" = "Shame says 'you're broken.' Compassion says 'you're human and healing.' Shame drives relapse. Compassion drives recovery. Choose compassion.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_45" = "Don't think about quitting forever—just win today. Tomorrow, win again. Chain enough days together and you've built a life you're proud of.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_46" = "Close your eyes. Inhale for 4, hold for 4, exhale for 8. Repeat 4 times. Long exhales activate your parasympathetic system and reduce the craving.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_47" = "Real human connection—eye contact, touch, conversation—satisfies needs that screens never will. The artificial version is a poor substitute. Seek the real thing.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_48" = "You're building discipline, self-respect, and neural pathways for self-control. Each day of resistance is a brick in the foundation. Don't knock it down.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_49" = "The easy choice provides instant relief and lasting regret. The hard choice provides instant discomfort and lasting pride. Choose the hard choice.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_50" = "Just 10 more minutes. Tell yourself you can give in after 10 minutes. When those pass, set another 10. Keep surfing the urge until it fades.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_51" = "Sunlight triggers serotonin, which competes with the craving for dopamine. Step outside for 5 minutes. Let the sun hit your face. Feel the shift.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_52" = "That sexual energy is just energy. Channel it into a workout, a creative project, cleaning, cooking—anything that produces something you're proud of.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_53" = "The you of next week is hoping you make the right choice right now. Don't let them down. They're counting on the strength you show in this moment.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_54" = "Life tests your commitment at the moments when giving up is easiest. This is a test. And you know the answer. Pass it. You've prepared for this.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_55" = "Drink a full glass of cold water slowly. The cold resets your nervous system, the act of drinking interrupts the craving, and the water hydrates your brain.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_56" = "You are not powerless. You've made thousands of choices today. This is just one more. And you have the ability to choose differently. Exercise that power.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_57" = "The urge promises pleasure but delivers emptiness. The regret is real, the shame is real, the time wasted is real. The pleasure? Gone in seconds.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_58" = "Stand up right now. Stretch your arms overhead. Touch your toes. Roll your neck. Physical movement changes your neurological state. Use your body to change your mind.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_59" = "Each 'no' to this urge strengthens your prefrontal cortex—the part of your brain responsible for self-control. You're literally building a stronger brain.";
"nudge_porn_addiction_detail_60" = "You are not defined by this habit. You are a whole person with dreams, values, and people who love you. This habit is something you do, not who you are. Let it go.";

