"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_33" = "You're rewriting your story. Keep going.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_34" = "Sparkling water in a nice glass. Try it.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_35" = "The first sip is where you lose control.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_36" = "Your body is healing every sober day.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_37" = "Boredom is not a reason to drink.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_38" = "You can do hard things sober.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_39" = "Make tonight the night you're proud of.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_40" = "Alcohol dulls everything, not just pain.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_41" = "You deserve mornings without regret.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_42" = "Go for a walk instead.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_43" = "The discomfort of not drinking passes.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_44" = "Count your sober days. Be proud.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_45" = "Every craving you survive makes you stronger.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_46" = "Your mental clarity is worth protecting.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_47" = "Reach out to someone who understands.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_48" = "You're not missing out. You're opting in to life.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_49" = "Tea, not beer. Try it tonight.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_50" = "Sobriety is freedom, not restriction.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_51" = "Remember why you started this journey.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_52" = "The morning version of you will be grateful.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_53" = "Deep breaths beat deep drinks.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_54" = "You can feel your feelings without numbing them.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_55" = "One more sober night. Stack the wins.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_56" = "Alcohol won't fix what's bothering you.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_57" = "Your brain chemistry is improving daily.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_58" = "Change the routine. Break the pattern.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_59" = "You're proving something tonight. To yourself.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_notification_60" = "Stay strong. One day at a time.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_15" = "The craving is just a signal—not a command. You can acknowledge it without obeying it. Say 'I notice I want a drink' and let the feeling sit. Don't act on it.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_16" = "Tomorrow's clarity, energy, and self-respect start with tonight's decision. Sober tonight means waking up clear, hydrated, and proud. Choose that version.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_17" = "Alcohol doesn't solve problems—it postpones them. Whatever you're trying to avoid will still be there tomorrow, plus a hangover. Face it now, sober and strong.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_18" = "The first drink activates neural pathways that demand more. 'Just one' is the most dangerous lie because one genuinely leads to many. Don't start.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_19" = "The sober version of you has better judgment. Trust that version. They know that tomorrow's regret isn't worth tonight's numbness.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_20" = "Your liver processes one standard drink per hour. Three drinks means three hours of toxic processing. Give your body the night off. It's working hard for you.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_21" = "Pour a glass of water right now. Drink it slowly. The act of drinking something satisfies part of the ritual. Replace the contents, keep the comfort.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_22" = "The craving says you need alcohol to relax, socialize, or sleep. All false. You did all those things before alcohol. You can do them without it.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_23" = "Fast forward to tomorrow morning: headache, dry mouth, guilt, foggy brain vs. clear head, energy, pride, and a good breakfast. Which morning do you want?";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_24" = "Each sober night adds to your streak—your proof that you're capable of change. Don't break the chain for a drink you won't even remember tomorrow.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_25" = "You're not depriving yourself of something good—you're choosing something better. Clarity over fog. Health over habit. Freedom over dependency.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_26" = "Isolation plus alcohol is a dangerous combination. Pick up the phone and call someone. The conversation will satisfy the real need—connection—better than any drink.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_27" = "Alcohol borrows serotonin from tomorrow. Tonight feels slightly better; tomorrow feels significantly worse. The interest rate is brutal. Stop borrowing.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_28" = "You are more than this habit. You have skills, relationships, and dreams that alcohol dulls. Every sober day sharpens your life back into focus.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_29" = "What triggered this craving? Stress? Boredom? Social pressure? Loneliness? Name the real trigger and address it directly. The drink is a decoy.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_30" = "Alcohol fragments sleep architecture, suppressing REM and deep sleep. Even a couple drinks ruin sleep quality. Sober sleep is genuinely restorative.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_31" = "Cravings peak at 10-20 minutes and then subside. Set a timer. Do anything else for 20 minutes. When it rings, the urge will be significantly weaker.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_32" = "Play the full tape: First drink feels good. Second drink, you lose judgment. Third drink, you say or do something regrettable. Morning: shame. See the whole movie.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_33" = "You're writing a new story—one where alcohol doesn't control your nights. Every sober evening is a new page. Keep writing. The story gets better.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_34" = "Pour sparkling water into your nicest glass. Add ice, a slice of lemon. The ritual matters more than the alcohol. Keep the ritual, lose the poison.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_35" = "Once the first sip happens, your prefrontal cortex (impulse control) weakens and your limbic system (more, more, more) takes over. Don't take the first sip.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_36" = "After 3 days sober: better sleep. After 1 week: clearer skin. After 2 weeks: more energy. After 1 month: significant liver recovery. Your body heals fast.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_37" = "Boredom is one of the top triggers. Have a go-to list ready: a show, a book, a walk, a game, a call. Boredom requires activity, not alcohol.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_38" = "Difficult emotions are part of being human. Feeling them—really feeling them—makes you stronger. Numbing them with alcohol just delays the inevitable.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_39" = "Tonight is an opportunity to prove something to the most important person: yourself. Wake up tomorrow with pride instead of regret.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_40" = "Alcohol doesn't just dull pain—it dulls joy, creativity, connection, and presence. You're not selectively numbing. You're numbing everything.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_41" = "Imagine waking up without a hangover: clear mind, no guilt, plenty of energy. That's available to you tonight. All you have to do is not pick up the glass.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_42" = "Put on shoes and go outside. A 15-minute walk releases endorphins that compete directly with the craving. Move your body and let chemistry do the rest.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_43" = "The discomfort of not drinking is temporary—it passes in minutes. The discomfort of drinking lasts hours (hangover) to years (health, relationships). Choose wisely.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_44" = "Count your sober days right now. Say the number out loud. That number represents commitment, strength, and growth. Add one more tonight.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_45" = "Every craving you survive without giving in literally rewires your brain. The neural pathway for 'craving → drink' weakens each time you choose differently.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_46" = "Alcohol clouds your thinking for up to 72 hours after drinking. Protecting your mental clarity tonight means sharper thinking for the next three days.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_47" = "You don't have to fight this alone. Text or call someone who understands—a friend, a sponsor, a support group. Vulnerability is not weakness; it's strategy.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_48" = "You're not missing out on fun—you're opting in to real life. Real conversations, real emotions, real memories. Drunk fun isn't real fun.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_49" = "Make a cup of herbal tea. Hold the warm mug. Sip slowly. The ritual of preparation and consumption satisfies similar neural pathways without the damage.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_50" = "Sobriety isn't a cage—it's the key. Alcohol was the cage: controlling your evenings, ruining your mornings, deciding your mood. You're free now. Stay free.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_51" = "Remember the moment you decided to change. What were you feeling? What did you want? That reason is still valid. Honor it tonight.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_52" = "When you wake up clear-headed tomorrow, you'll feel a deep gratitude for tonight's decision. Give your morning self that gift. They deserve it.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_53" = "Inhale slowly for 4 counts. Hold for 7. Exhale for 8. Repeat 3 times. This activates your parasympathetic nervous system and reduces the craving.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_54" = "Feelings are signals, not threats. Sadness, anger, anxiety—they're information. You can sit with them, learn from them, and let them pass. You don't need to drown them.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_55" = "One more sober night. That's all you need to commit to. Not forever, not next month. Just tonight. Stack enough tonights and you've changed your life.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_56" = "Alcohol is a depressant that temporarily mimics relief. The anxiety or sadness you're trying to escape will be worse tomorrow with alcohol in the equation.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_57" = "Your GABA receptors are recalibrating, your serotonin is rebalancing, your dopamine baseline is rising. Every sober day, your brain chemistry improves.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_58" = "If you always drink at 8 PM on the couch, change the routine: go for a walk at 7:45, sit in a different spot, start a new show. Breaking patterns breaks habits.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_59" = "Tonight, you're proving to yourself that you can do this. Not for anyone else—for you. That self-trust compounds into unshakeable confidence over time.";
"nudge_alcohol_dependency_detail_60" = "One day at a time. That's all sobriety asks. Today, you don't drink. Tomorrow, you make the same choice. Eventually, it's just who you are. Keep going.";

